Epigyne (Fig. 78
E-G
): broad (Fig. 78E). Inner structure partially visible through the tegument (Fig. 78E). Scape short and very wide. Lateral grooves distinct and curved (Fig. 78E). Spermathecae small, globular, separated by less than 2.5 diameters (Fig. 78G). Fertilization ducts thin, long and proximally coiled into less than two loops and distally straight (Fig. 78G). Copulatory ducts broad, divided into two parts, the ovoid inner part shorter than the compressed outer part (Fig. 78G).
